The contract required by this section:
shall state the rates, terms, and purposes of commissions, charges, and other fees that the reinsurance manager may impose against the reinsurer; and
shall provide that:
the reinsurer shall have reasonable access to and the right to copy all accounts and records maintained by the reinsurance manager that relate to business transactions with the reinsurer;
the reinsurance manager shall maintain accounts and records in a form usable by the reinsurer;
the reinsurance manager may not retain for more than 3 months estimated claims payments and allocated loss adjustment expenses;
